      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>We come to you with <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/there-will-be-more-derailments/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">an urgent follow-up</a> to yesterday's train derailment story, detailing how Pete Buttigieg‚Äôs Transportation Department has no plans to reinstate a brake safety rule touted by its own experts ‚Äî but is considering a separate, industry-backed proposal to weaken existing train brake rules.</p><p>Also:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://share.transistor.fm/s/f3d5e423\">Click here to listen</a> to <em>The Lever</em>'s Julia Rock and Rebecca Burns discuss their reporting on this issue in detail.</li><li>If you or anyone you know has been directly affected by the train derailment disaster, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:tips@levernews.com\">tips@levernews.com</a> ‚Äî we want to hear your story.</li></ul><p>Spread the word: Forward this email to encourage others <a href=\"https://levernews.com/membership/?utm_source=daily&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=forward-signup\">to subscribe to <em>The Lever</em></a>.</p><p>Rock the boat.</p>"
      },
